abstract = "Background
The effects of subinhibitory concentrations (sub-MICs) of antibacterial agents on the biofilm-forming ability of Staphylococcus aureus remain understudied. We investigated the effects of sub-MICs of chlorhexidine and mupirocin on biofilm formation in clinical methicillin-resistant Staphylococcus aureus (MRSA) isolates.
Methods
