The four strains were susceptible to colistin, ciprofloxacin, ceftazidime–avibactam, and ceftolozane–tazobactam. blaSHV2a was identified in each genome of this ST235-O11 serotype cluster that showed an identical cgMLST profile (0–2 out of 4162 different alleles). The phylogenic analysis of 162 ST235 genomes showed that only four other strains harboured a blaSHV2a, originating from France and USA, clustering together although being different from the outbreak strains.
