PPS data were reported for 171,116 patients. Annual prevalence of patients with HCAI with onset during hospitalization decreased from 6.1% in 2007 to 3.6% in 2016. The adjusted odds ratio (OR) for trend was 0.97 (95% confidence interval: 0.96–0.98). Most prominent trends were seen for surgical site infections (1.6%–0.8%; OR: 0.91 (0.90–0.93)) and urinary tract infections (2.1%–0.6%; OR: 0.85 (0.83–0.87)). From 2014 on, HCAIs at admission were also registered with a stable prevalence of approximately 1.5%. The mean length of stay decreased from 10 to 7 days. The percentage of patients treated with antibiotics increased from 31% to 36% (OR: 1.03 (1.02–1.03)).
