The median days of therapy in the group aged 16–65 years were 7.24 for tertiary hospitals, 3.28 for secondary acute care hospitals, and 1.42 for fee-for-service hospitals. The median days of therapy of the group aged >65 years were 17.28 for tertiary hospitals, 14.43 for secondary acute care hospitals, and 8.21 for fee-for-service hospitals. For multivariable linear regression analyses, each model selected a different combination of covariates from the potential predictors based on hospital characteristics.
