Hip and knee arthroplasty procedures were performed on artificial foam bone, which was continuously kept wet with a marker fluid. Each of the procedures was carried out by ten subjects wearing conventional surgical clothing or wearing SHS with integrated toga. After the simulated operation, pictures of the subjects were taken under ultraviolet illumination. Images wearing the full gown, and after removal of the gown, were evaluated for stained areas.
